    "name": "Popa Wu",
    "profile": "Popa Wu (also known as Freedum/ [a=Freedom Allah] was a [a=Wu-Tang Clan]–affiliated artist, spoken-word performer, and de facto spiritual mentor to the group, closely tied to the Nation of Gods & Earths. He appeared on key Wu-Tang and solo records—most notably “Wu-Revolution” (Wu-Tang Forever), Ghostface Killah’s “All That I Got Is You,” and Raekwon’s “North Star (Jewels).” He also issued the compilations Visions Of The 10th Chamber (2000) and Visions Of The 10th Chamber Pt. II (2008). A cousin of [a=RZA] (and related to [a=GZA] and [a=Ol' Dirty Bastard]), Popa Wu was long regarded as the Clan’s elder and counselor, often building on Five-Percenter mathematics and lessons between tracks and at live shows. \r\nHe died on December 16, 2019, aged 63. Tributes from the group and the wider hip-hop community followed; no official cause of death was made public.",
